---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Actions" current="actions">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Actions</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Things to do before and during the tour. Check them off as you go — state is local to your browser.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Before Departure (April – May)</h2>

  <ul class="checklist" id="checklist-pre">
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a1" />
      <span>
        <strong>Email French Embassy Wellington</strong> re: NZ bilateral visa waiver agreement<br/>
        <span class="priority">Sent to drafts</span> · information.wellington-amba@diplomatie.gouv.fr · 
        Confirm agreement is still active, ask about EES process, what documentation to carry
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a2" />
      <span>
        <strong>Book flight London → Tbilisi</strong><br/>
        Wizz Air typically cheapest · target ~May 16–18 · bikes as checked luggage (check policy)
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a3" />
      <span>
        <strong>Fork purchase decision</strong><br/>
        Fox 36 SL (130mm) recommended over RockShox SID for reliability on a 5-month tour. 
        FIT4 damper more forgiving of missed service intervals. ~200-300g heavier, negligible on a loaded rig.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a4" />
      <span>
        <strong>Full bike service</strong><br/>
        New chain, cassette assessment, fresh brake pads, fork full service (zero the clock), 
        wheel true, hub service. Start the tour at zero hours on everything.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a5" />
      <span>
        <strong>Buy fork service kit</strong><br/>
        200hr kit for whichever fork you choose. Dust seals, foam rings, o-rings. 
        Not available in Turkey/Albania — buy before departure.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a6" />
      <span>
        <strong>Practice lower leg service</strong><br/>
        20-30 min job. Watch YouTube guides for your specific fork model. 
        Do it once at home so you're confident on the road.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a7" />
      <span>
        <strong>Buy spare folding tire</strong><br/>
        No MTB tire availability in eastern Turkey or Albania. Carry one spare from the start.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a8" />
      <span>
        <strong>Download offline maps</strong><br/>
        Maps.me (essential for Turkey/Balkans), Komoot, Gaia GPS. 
        Swiss Mobility app for Switzerland. Download all regions before departure.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a9" />
      <span>
        <strong>Download GPX files</strong><br/>
        Caucasus Crossing (bikepacking.com), Cappadocia Delight, Wolf's Lair, Trans-Dolomiti, 
        Zillertal Trail, TNR route collection (Komoot), Alps Divide sections
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a10" />
      <span>
        <strong>Install Schengen tracker app</strong><br/>
        schengen90.app or similar. Log entry/exit dates religiously. 
        Input France stay (Jan 17 – Apr 7) as historical data.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a11" />
      <span>
        <strong>Print bilateral agreement page</strong><br/>
        Print the French Embassy's own statement from nz.diplomatie.gouv.fr confirming 
        the NZ bilateral agreement. Carry as paper backup for border agents.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="a12" />
      <span>
        <strong>Sell possessions in UK</strong><br/>
        You have April 8 – mid-May. Budget the time.
      </span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>On the Road</h2>

  <ul class="checklist" id="checklist-road">
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="b1" />
      <span>
        <strong>Buy Turkish SIM (Turkcell)</strong><br/>
        Buy in first proper town, NOT at the border (rip-off pricing). 
        Turkcell has best rural coverage.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="b2" />
      <span>
        <strong>Check Georgia pass conditions</strong><br/>
        Abano Pass (Tusheti road) and Juta/Chaukhi — ask locally in Stepantsminda. 
        Late May is early; snow is likely at 3,000m+.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="b3" />
      <span>
        <strong>Register at Shatili army checkpoint</strong><br/>
        Required paperwork for the hiking trail areas near the Chechen border.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="b4" />
      <span>
        <strong>Fork lower leg service #1</strong><br/>
        ~3 weeks in (end of Georgia / start of Turkey). Clean foam rings, refresh oil bath.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="b5" />
      <span>
        <strong>Book Dolomites fork service</strong><br/>
        Full damper service at a suspension shop in Bolzano or Brixen. 
        Research shops before arriving — book ahead in September (busy season).
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="b6" />
      <span>
        <strong>Chain & cassette check at Dolomites</strong><br/>
        ~3-4 months in, ~4,000km+. Replace chain at minimum. 
        Assess cassette wear. Good bike shops in Bolzano/Brixen/Innsbruck.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="b7" />
      <span>
        <strong>Monitor Alps weather from late September</strong><br/>
        High passes (2,500m+) can get early snow mid-October. 
        TNR sections (Assietta, Little Peru) at 2,300-2,500m — check forecasts daily.
        Have bail-out plans for each high section.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="b8" />
      <span>
        <strong>Decision point: Nice</strong><br/>
        Schengen days exhausted? Embassy confirmed bilateral? → Ride on in France.<br/>
        No bilateral? → Book flight Nice → NZ.
      </span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Bookings & Reservations</h2>

  <ul class="checklist" id="checklist-bookings">
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="c1" />
      <span>
        <strong>Ferry: Bar (Montenegro) → Bari (Italy)</strong><br/>
        ~€40-60 with bike · ~9hrs overnight · Book a few days ahead in August (busy)
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <input type="checkbox" id="c2" />
      <span>
        <strong>Flight: Nice/Marseille → NZ</strong><br/>
        Book when ready. Open-ended departure — watch for deals.
      </span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <script>
    // Persist checkbox state in localStorage
    document.querySelectorAll('.checklist input[type="checkbox"]').forEach(cb => {
      const key = `action-${cb.id}`;
      cb.checked = localStorage.getItem(key) === 'true';
      cb.addEventListener('change', () => {
        localStorage.setItem(key, cb.checked.toString());
      });
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
